## 🌐 RTL (Right-to-Left) RULES

### ❌ NEVER:
- Use `marginLeft`, `marginRight`, `paddingLeft`, `paddingRight` in styles
- Use `left`, `right` positioning in styles
- Use `textAlign: 'left'` or `textAlign: 'right'` in styles

### ✅ ALWAYS:
- Use NativeWind classes that auto-flip: `ml-4`, `pr-2`, `text-left`
- Test in BOTH English (LTR) and Hebrew (RTL)
- Use flexbox for layouts (auto-adapts to RTL)

### What Auto-Flips:
- ✅ Margins: `ml-*` ↔ `mr-*`
- ✅ Padding: `pl-*` ↔ `pr-*`
- ✅ Text align: `text-left` ↔ `text-right`
- ✅ Flex direction: `flex-row` reverses

### What Doesn't Flip:
- ❌ Absolute positioning: `left-0`, `right-0`
- ❌ Border radius corners: `rounded-tl-*`

