## 🔧 BACKEND RULES

### ❌ NEVER:
- Put business logic in controllers
- Access data directly from controllers
- Return inconsistent response formats

### ✅ ALWAYS:
- Keep controllers thin (HTTP layer only)
- Put business logic in services
- Use consistent ApiResponse format:
  ```typescript
  {
    success: boolean;
    data?: T;
    error?: string;
    message?: string;
  }
  ```
- Use dependency injection: `constructor(private readonly service: Service)`

---

## 📦 SHARED PACKAGE RULES

### ❌ NEVER:
- Define types separately in frontend and backend
- Use `any` types in shared package
- Put business logic in shared package

### ✅ ALWAYS:
- Define ALL entity types in `packages/shared/src/types/`
- Define DTOs (Data Transfer Objects) in shared types
- Import from shared: `import { Group, CreateGroupDto } from '@cost-share/shared'`
- Keep shared package pure (types, schemas, utils only)

