## 🎯 LOADING PATTERN

### ✅ ALWAYS:
- Use `useLoading()` hook for loading states:
  ```typescript
  import { useLoading } from '../../hooks/useLoading';
  
  const { isLoading, startLoading, stopLoading } = useLoading();
  
  const loadData = async () => {
    startLoading();
    await fetchData();
    stopLoading();
  };
  ```
- Use `LoadingIndicator` component for UI:
  ```typescript
  import { LoadingIndicator } from '../../components/LoadingIndicator';
  
  if (isLoading) {
    return <LoadingIndicator />;
  }
  
  // Or with custom message:
  if (isLoading) {
    return <LoadingIndicator message={t('groups.loadingGroups')} />;
  }
  ```

### ❌ NEVER:
- Don't write loading UI inline - use LoadingIndicator component
- Don't use global loading state from store

---

## 📝 CODE QUALITY RULES

### ❌ NEVER:
- Leave console.logs in production code (except error logging)
- Use magic numbers (use constants)
- Write functions longer than 50 lines
- Nest code more than 3 levels deep

### ✅ ALWAYS:
- Add file header comments explaining purpose
- Document complex functions
- Use early returns to reduce nesting
- Extract complex logic into separate functions
- Use meaningful variable names
- Group imports logically (external, internal, types)

---

## 🔍 TESTING CHECKLIST

Before completing any task, verify:

- [ ] No inline styles (except RTL icon transforms)
- [ ] No hardcoded strings (all use `t()`)
- [ ] No "any" types
- [ ] All imports resolve correctly
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors
- [ ] Translations added to BOTH en.json AND he.json
- [ ] Colors from theme, not hardcoded
- [ ] API calls only in services/
- [ ] Follows service layer pattern
- [ ] Tested in English (LTR)
- [ ] Tested in Hebrew (RTL)

